WEBVTT

00:01.060 --> 00:02.322
PREVIOUSLY
ON "VERONICA MARS"...

00:02.370 --> 00:03.928
THIS HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH US.

00:03.970 --> 00:06.188
YOUR SECRET, ILLEGITIMATE CHILD
AFFECTS NEITHER YOU NOR ME.

00:06.240 --> 00:10.006
I FOUND THEM
IN MY DAUGHTER'S ROOM.
WE WERE TRYING
TO HELP GRACE.

00:10.040 --> 00:12.907
THEY'VE BEEN ABUSING HER. THEY
HAD HER LOCKED IN THE CLOSET.

00:12.940 --> 00:14.237
THEIR ADOPTION CONTRACTS

00:14.280 --> 00:16.601
ARE ALL ABOUT
RELIGIOUS INDOCTRINATION.

00:16.650 --> 00:18.572
WHEN I THINK OF MY CHILD
BROUGHT UP LIKE THAT...

00:18.610 --> 00:20.373
ASTRID,
IF YOU'RE DONE GAPING...

00:20.420 --> 00:21.876
HOW CAN YOU
PUT UP WITH HER?

00:21.920 --> 00:23.979
SHE PROMISED TO PAY MY WAY
THROUGH GRAD SCHOOL.

00:24.020 --> 00:25.317
WE'RE LEAVING NOW.

00:25.350 --> 00:27.056
HONEY, THERE'S SOMETHING
I NEED TO TELL YOU.

00:27.090 --> 00:28.057
MEG DIED.

00:28.090 --> 00:29.455
THE BABY?

00:29.490 --> 00:31.128
SHE SURVIVED.

00:42.000 --> 00:44.059
HI, HO.

00:45.870 --> 00:47.303
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

00:47.340 --> 00:48.602
OH, YOUR UNIFORM.

00:53.350 --> 00:55.341
I GUESS THAT MAKES ME
SNOW WHITE.

00:55.380 --> 00:57.985
YOU MUST BE ON YOUR WAY UP
TO SEE MOPEY.

00:58.020 --> 00:59.419
HOW'S HE DOING, SLEAZY?

00:59.460 --> 01:01.485
WOULDN'T KNOW.
HE DOESN'T COME OUT OF HIS ROOM.

01:01.520 --> 01:04.421
OLD ITALIAN LADIES
DON'T GRIEVE LIKE THIS.

01:05.360 --> 01:08.193
BOY, HE MUST HAVE
REALLY LOVED MEG.

01:08.230 --> 01:10.323
WELL, THEN THERE'S
THAT OTHER THING --

01:10.370 --> 01:12.292
YOU KNOW,
HE CAN'T SEE HIS BABY.

01:12.340 --> 01:14.865
A BABY?
HOW'D THAT HAPPEN?

01:15.370 --> 01:17.429
[ ELEVATOR DINGS ]

01:26.720 --> 01:30.440
THERE SHE GOES --
THE ANGEL OF MERCY.

01:30.490 --> 01:33.482
TIME TO FAKE THE DOUGHNUT.

01:35.690 --> 01:36.782
UH-OH.

01:36.830 --> 01:38.980
DID YOU CATCH HIM
WAXING HIS BOARD?

01:39.030 --> 01:41.248
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:43.570 --> 01:46.232
I WAS INVITED.
HOW ABOUT YOU?

01:59.950 --> 02:01.508
LOST?

02:03.490 --> 02:04.980
OH, QUIT STANDING THERE
SO SMUG.

02:05.020 --> 02:07.250
TOMORROW YOU'RE JUST GONNA
CALL ME AT 2:00 IN THE MORNING

02:07.290 --> 02:09.258
SAYING YOU WANT
SOME COMPANY.

02:09.290 --> 02:10.621
FOR YOUR INFORMATION,

02:10.660 --> 02:13.128
THAT REALLY DOESN'T
SATISFY ME, LOGAN.

02:13.160 --> 02:16.197
REALLY?
YOU ALWAYS COME.

02:25.740 --> 02:27.776
LOGAN TOLD ME
WHAT HAPPENED.

02:27.810 --> 02:30.244
YOU GOT TO LET IT GO,
RONNIE.

02:30.280 --> 02:32.441
TAKE A DEEP BREATH
AND LET IT GO.

02:32.480 --> 02:35.244
IF YOU'RE GONNA DATE
AN HEIR TO BILLIONS,

02:35.280 --> 02:37.043
THE OCCASIONAL
AFI'ERNOON QUICKIE --

02:37.090 --> 02:39.388
YOU GOT TO
LET IT SLIDE.

02:39.420 --> 02:40.785
COST OF DOING BUSINESS,
YOU KNOW?

02:40.820 --> 02:42.481
SERIOUSLY,
GIRLS LIKE KENDALL --

02:42.530 --> 02:44.555
THEY LET YOU DO THINGS
THAT GIRLS LIKE YOU --

02:44.590 --> 02:47.457
WELL, LET'S JUST SAY,
YOU SHOULD BE THANKFUL.

02:47.500 --> 02:50.162
VILE STUFF, YOU KNOW,
REALLY VILE STUFF.

02:50.200 --> 02:51.599
MOVE, DICK.

02:51.630 --> 02:53.791
JUST TRYING
TO BE HELPFUL.

03:04.280 --> 03:07.249
SO, WHERE WERE YOU
YESTERDAY?

03:07.280 --> 03:08.611
I STAYED HOME.

03:08.650 --> 03:11.039
NO, YOU DIDN'T.
I CAME BY.

03:11.090 --> 03:14.412
I STAYED HOME, THEN IN THE
AFI'ERNOON, I WENT FOR A DRIVE.

03:14.460 --> 03:16.678
I CALLED YOUR CELL
10 TIMES.

03:16.730 --> 03:18.186
I HAD IT TURNED OFF.

03:18.230 --> 03:19.697
YEAH,
I FIGURED THAT OUT.

03:19.730 --> 03:21.925
GOD, WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?
I NEEDED SOME TIME TO THINK.

03:21.960 --> 03:24.793
MY PROBLEM STARTS WITH FINDING
KENDALL IN YOUR SHOWER.

03:24.830 --> 03:27.936
KENDALL? SHE PROBABLY
GOT THE BEDROOMS CONFUSED.

03:27.970 --> 03:30.302
DON'T LIE TO ME!
I TRUSTED YOU THE FIRST TIME.

03:30.340 --> 03:33.503
BUT NOT ANYMORE.
I'M NOBODY'S FOOL.

03:33.540 --> 03:36.304
PERFECT. MEG'S DEAD.
I CAN'T SEE MY DAUGHTER.

03:36.350 --> 03:37.703
BUT LET'S MAKE THIS
ABOUT YOU.

03:37.750 --> 03:39.547
WHY SHOULDN'T IT BE
LIKE ANY OTHER DAY?

03:39.580 --> 03:41.639
GOD, SHUT UP
ABOUT MEG ALREADY!

03:41.680 --> 03:44.649
I'M ALIVE!
I'M YOUR GIRLFRIEND!

03:47.020 --> 03:48.578
NOT ANYMORE.

04:12.850 --> 04:16.411
[ AL GREEN'S "HOW CAN YOU MEND
A BROKEN HEART?" PLAYS ]

04:31.500 --> 04:33.991
* I CAN THINK OF YOUNGER DAYS

04:35.770 --> 04:39.706
* WHEN LIVING FOR MY LIFE

04:41.040 --> 04:46.000
* WAS EVERYTHING
A MAN COULD WANT TO DO *

04:48.780 --> 04:53.251
* I COULD NEVER SEE

04:53.290 --> 04:59.399
* TOMORROW

04:59.430 --> 05:03.218
* I WAS NEVER TOLD

05:03.270 --> 05:10.108
* ABOUT THE SORROW

05:10.140 --> 05:13.598
* AND

05:13.640 --> 05:20.045
* HOW CAN YOU
MEND A BROKEN HEART? *

05:20.080 --> 05:22.446
[ THE HOLLIES'
"THE AIR THAT I BREATHE" PLAYS ]

05:22.490 --> 05:25.345
* NOTHING TO EAT

05:25.390 --> 05:30.521
* NO BOOKS TO READ

05:30.560 --> 05:34.758
* MAKING LOVE WITH YOU

05:34.800 --> 05:37.462
* HAS LEFI' ME PEACEFUL

05:37.500 --> 05:39.297
Keith: VERONICA.

05:39.330 --> 05:42.231
SORRY,
I'LL TURN IT DOWN.

05:42.270 --> 05:43.567
I'M COMING IN.

05:43.610 --> 05:46.704
* WHAT MORE COULD I ASK?

05:46.740 --> 05:50.403
* THERE'S NOTHING LEFI'

05:50.450 --> 05:51.747
HONEY.

05:51.780 --> 05:53.077
I'M OKAY.

05:54.850 --> 05:58.786
YOU REMEMBER I'M A DETECTIVE,
RIGHT, A PRETTY GOOD ONE?

06:02.590 --> 06:05.127
DUNCAN AND I BROKE UP.

06:05.160 --> 06:06.696
YEAH, I GOT THAT.

06:06.730 --> 06:09.392
IS THERE ANYTHING
I CAN DO?

06:10.800 --> 06:12.529
THAN KS.

06:12.570 --> 06:15.562
REALLY I JUST NEED
SOME TIME.

06:15.600 --> 06:18.831
ANYTHING YOU NEED, HONEY,
I'M HERE.

06:18.870 --> 06:23.739
* ALL I NEED
IS THE AIR THAT I BREATHE *

06:23.780 --> 06:27.238
* AND TO LOVE YOU

06:27.280 --> 06:32.308
* ALL I NEED
IS THE AIR THAT I BREATHE *

06:32.350 --> 06:35.786
* YES, TO LOVE YOU

06:35.820 --> 06:39.381
IT'S DOWN TO TWO GUYS --
HECTOR OR BOOTSY.

06:39.430 --> 06:41.421
ONE OF THEM
STABBED FELIX.

06:41.460 --> 06:42.768
THUMPER SAYS
THEY WERE THE ONLY TWO

06:42.800 --> 06:44.495
LEFI' ON THE BRIDGE
WITH YOU AND HIM.

06:44.530 --> 06:46.691
SO, HOW WE GONNA FIGURE OUT
WHO DID IT?

06:46.740 --> 06:48.196
THE ONE THAT DID IT

06:48.240 --> 06:49.798
IS THE ONE WHO'S IN BUSINESS
WITH THE FITZPATRICKS.

06:49.840 --> 06:52.365
HE'S GOT A PIPELINE
OF COKE, METH, "E."

06:52.410 --> 06:53.604
YOU KNOW ANYONE WHO CAN --

06:53.640 --> 06:55.676
YEAH. I'LL HANDLE IT.

06:56.550 --> 07:01.010
* I DON'T WANT TO WAIT
FOR OUR LIVES TO BE OVER *

07:01.050 --> 07:03.985
Wallace:
OH, THAT'S JUST PATHETIC.

07:05.320 --> 07:06.912
UP! GET UP!

07:06.960 --> 07:09.349
I CAME OVER HERE
TO SEE VERONICA MARS.

07:09.390 --> 07:10.721
WHO'S THIS EMO GIRL?

07:10.760 --> 07:12.728
LEAVE ME ALONE.
I'M WALLOWING.

07:12.760 --> 07:15.251
NOT ANYMORE.
WE'RE GOING OUT.

07:15.300 --> 07:18.895
WE GOT TO GO SEE A MOVIE OR
GET IN A BAR FIGHT OR SOMETHING.

07:18.930 --> 07:20.693
I DON'T WANT TO
GET IN A BAR FIGHT.

07:20.740 --> 07:22.799
TOUGH, 'CAUSE YOU'RE GOING
IF I HAVE TO DRAG YOU.

07:22.840 --> 07:26.207
BUT BEFORE WE DO,
VERONICA, SHOWER.

07:26.240 --> 07:27.400
YOU SMELL BAD.

07:27.440 --> 07:28.771
YOU'RE NOT HELPING.

07:28.810 --> 07:30.607
YOU THINK YOU'RE HELPING,
BUT YOU'RE NOT.

07:30.650 --> 07:32.948
YOU'LL BE NEEDING THIS.
AND WHAT'S THAT?

07:32.980 --> 07:35.619
A TICKET TO TOMORROW NIGHT'S
BASKETBALL GAME.

07:35.650 --> 07:37.811
AH, HE REVEALS
HIS TRUE COLORS.

07:37.850 --> 07:40.751
THAT'S RIGHT.
I BLEED THE GOLD AND GREEN.

07:40.790 --> 07:43.623
I'M A PIRATE BORN,
A PIRATE BRED,

07:43.660 --> 07:45.321
AND WHEN ME DIE --

07:45.360 --> 07:46.759
A PIRATE DEAD?

07:46.800 --> 07:49.394
BIG TALK FROM A GUY WHO
ONLY MOVED BACK TO NEPTUNE

07:49.430 --> 07:51.295
TO PLAY BALL.

07:51.330 --> 07:52.866
IF YOUR CHICAGO HIGH SCHOOL

07:52.900 --> 07:54.561
HADN'T HAD THEIR TRYOUTS LAST
YEAR, YOU'D STILL BE THERE.

07:54.600 --> 07:56.033
AND IF IFS AND BUTS
WERE CANDY AND NUTS,

07:56.070 --> 07:57.662
WE'D ALL HAVE
A MERRY CHRISTMAS.

07:57.710 --> 07:59.007
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

07:59.040 --> 08:01.634
NO CLUE.
SOMETHING MY MOM SAYS.

08:01.680 --> 08:04.240
Keith:
VERONICA, CAN YOU COME HERE?

08:06.550 --> 08:08.518
HONEY,
DUNCAN'S MISSING.

08:08.550 --> 08:10.438
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
HE'S MISSING?

08:10.490 --> 08:12.117
HE'S TAKEN --

08:12.150 --> 08:14.459
HE'S KIDNAPPED THE MANNING BABY,
BUT YOU ALREADY KNOW, DON'T YOU?

08:14.490 --> 08:15.479
WHAT?

08:15.520 --> 08:16.748
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST

08:16.790 --> 08:18.189
AS AN ACCOMPLICE
IN THE ABDUCTION

08:18.230 --> 08:21.051
AND THE DISAPPEARANCE
OF FAITH MANNING.

08:26.070 --> 08:30.029
* A LONG TIME AGO,
WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

08:30.070 --> 08:35.599
* BUT I HAVEN'T THOUGHT OF YOU
LATELY AT ALL *

08:36.440 --> 08:38.146
* COME ON, NOW, SUGAR

08:38.180 --> 08:40.671
* BRING IT ON, BRING IT ON,
YEAH *

08:40.720 --> 08:44.178
* JUST REMEMBER ME WHEN

08:44.220 --> 08:49.385
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS
A LONG TIME AGO *

08:49.420 --> 08:51.285
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS

08:51.330 --> 08:56.666
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

09:16.890 --> 09:19.313
Man:
NUMBER FIVE, STEP FORWARD.

09:30.570 --> 09:31.821
WHAT WAS THAT ALL ABOUT?

09:31.870 --> 09:33.690
YOU WERE PICKED
OUT OF THE LINEUP

09:33.740 --> 09:36.038
BY A MERCHANT FROM
THE L.A. JEWELRY DISTRICT.

09:36.070 --> 09:38.209
OH.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, OH?

09:38.240 --> 09:40.379
I WAS EXPECTING SHOCK
AND INDIGNATION.

09:40.410 --> 09:42.605
YEAH, I KNOW
WHAT THEY MUST BE THINKING.

09:42.650 --> 09:46.438
THE WITNESS CLAIMS YOU SOLD HIM
SOME 5-KARAT DIAMOND EARRINGS

09:46.480 --> 09:47.879
FOR $80,000,

09:47.920 --> 09:49.888
EARRINGS THAT
BELONGED TO CELESTE KANE.

09:49.920 --> 09:51.615
THE SHERIFF
THINKS YOU'RE AN ACCOMPLICE

09:51.650 --> 09:55.086
AND THAT YOU HELPED DUNCAN PLAN
AND FINANCE THIS KIDNAPPING.

09:55.120 --> 09:57.520
THAT'S A LOT OF THINKING
FOR LAMB.

09:57.560 --> 09:59.187
HE MAY TIRE HIMSELF OUT.

09:59.230 --> 10:02.495
THIS IS NOT A JOKE.
THIS IS KIDNAPPING.

10:02.530 --> 10:04.293
WHAT DUNCAN'S DONE
IS WRONG,

10:04.330 --> 10:07.663
AND IF YOU'VE HELPED HIM IN
ANY WAY, YOU'RE GOING TO PRISON.

10:07.700 --> 10:09.463
NOW, STRAIGHTEN UP.

10:09.500 --> 10:12.105
I DID SELL THE EARRINGS --
DUNCAN ASKED ME TO --

10:12.140 --> 10:14.131
BUT NOT TO FINANCE
A KIDNAPPING.

10:14.180 --> 10:15.477
WE HAD A PLAN.

10:15.510 --> 10:16.909
A PLAN?

10:16.950 --> 10:19.544
A PLAN TO GET CUSTODY
OF THE BABY...

10:19.580 --> 10:21.138
LEGALLY.

10:21.180 --> 10:23.341
DUNCAN WANTED TO HIRE A LAWYER,
BUT HE NEEDED MONEY.

10:23.390 --> 10:25.415
DID YOU KNOW THE EARRINGS
WERE CELESTE'S?

10:25.450 --> 10:27.315
I DIDN'T ASK.
VERONICA.

10:27.360 --> 10:28.782
I FIGURED THEY WERE,

10:28.820 --> 10:31.220
BUT HIS PARENTS
DIDN'T WANT DUNCAN ADOPTING.

10:31.260 --> 10:34.149
CELESTE ISN'T QUITE READY
TO BE A GRANDMOTHER.

10:34.200 --> 10:36.054
VERONICA,
LISTEN TO ME CLEARLY.

10:36.100 --> 10:37.863
YOU'RE GONNA
COOPERATE WITH LAMB.

10:37.900 --> 10:41.199
YOU'RE GONNA ANSWER EVERY
QUESTION HE ASKS, TRUTHFULLY.

10:41.240 --> 10:44.266
AND WHEN DUNCAN KANE IS FOUND --
AND HE WILL BE FOUND --

10:44.310 --> 10:47.837
THERE'S GONNA BE NO DOUBT WHOSE
SIDE YOU WERE ON IN ALL THIS.

10:47.880 --> 10:49.370
UNDERSTOOD?

10:52.010 --> 10:54.069
HERE'S VERONICA
FOR YOU.

10:54.120 --> 10:56.372
HEY, VERONICA,
WHAT'S THE HAPS?

10:56.420 --> 10:59.514
OH, YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T THINK
THERE'D BE AIR CONDITIONING,

10:59.550 --> 11:03.088
BUT OTHER THAN THAT, THIS IS
PRETI'Y MUCH HOW I PICTURED HELL.

11:03.130 --> 11:05.451
SHE KNOWS WHERE MY SON IS,
SHERIFF.

11:05.490 --> 11:06.957
I GUARANTEE IT.

11:07.000 --> 11:09.525
IF SHE DOESN'T COOPERATE FULLY,
I WANT HER PROSECUTED

11:09.560 --> 11:12.734
FOR HER INVOLVEMENT
IN THE THEFT OF MY JEWELRY.

11:12.770 --> 11:14.590
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

11:14.640 --> 11:17.131
BIG CASE,
MISSING PERSON.

11:17.170 --> 11:19.263
SO, WHERE DO YOU
GOT HIM STASHED?

11:19.310 --> 11:22.199
ALL RIGHT, ENOUGH.
I'LL ASK THE QUESTIONS.

11:22.240 --> 11:24.470
YOU'RE ONLY HERE
AS A GUEST OF MRS. KANE.

11:24.510 --> 11:27.411
MRS. KANE, A WORD OF ADVICE --
PRIVATE INVESTIGATORS

11:27.450 --> 11:30.419
MAKE THE WORK OF LAW ENFORCEMENT
OFFICERS MORE DIFFICULT.

11:30.450 --> 11:31.940
SAVE YOUR MONEY.

11:31.990 --> 11:34.709
WE'LL FIND DUNCAN.
WE'LL BRING HIM IN SAFELY.

11:36.060 --> 11:38.528
IT'S KIND OF WEIRD,
HUH,

11:38.560 --> 11:41.620
HOPING LAMB IS COMPETENT
RATHER THAN BE'ITING HE'S NOT?

11:41.660 --> 11:45.426
KEEP ME POSTED
ON ANY DEVELOPMENTS.

11:47.170 --> 11:50.162
I FIND COMFORT IN KNOWING
THE CHILD ISN'T YOURS.

11:50.210 --> 11:52.303
LET'S HOPE
SHE'S GOT YOUR SMILE.

11:52.340 --> 11:53.876
MR. VAN LOWE.

12:08.820 --> 12:10.754
SIT.

12:15.560 --> 12:17.664
WRITE DOWN EVERYTHING
YOU CAN THINK OF.

12:17.700 --> 12:19.258
YOU KNOW
WHAT I'M LOOKING FOR --

12:19.300 --> 12:21.666
FAKE I.D.s,
SECRET CREDIT CARDS,

12:21.700 --> 12:23.702
HIDING SPOTS,
FAVORITE RESTAURANTS,

12:23.740 --> 12:27.403
ANYONE WHO MIGHT LET HIM BORROW
A CAR OR A VACATION HOME.

12:27.440 --> 12:28.907
LET ME ASK YOU A QUESTION.

12:28.940 --> 12:32.546
DO YOU THINK THE BABY
IS BETTER OFF NOW WITH DUNCAN

12:32.580 --> 12:33.808
OR WITH THE MANNINGS?

12:33.850 --> 12:35.442
I SHOULD HAVE BUSTED YOU
THAT NIGHT.

12:35.480 --> 12:37.687
NOW MY ASS IS IN A SLING
IF I DON'T FIND THE KANE KID.

12:37.720 --> 12:40.359
YOU'RE NOT GOING HOME TONIGHT
UNLESS THAT PAD IS FULL.

12:40.390 --> 12:44.224
WHEN THIS IS ALL OVER,
IF YOU LEFI' ANYTHING OFF,

12:44.260 --> 12:48.094
I WILL MAKE IT MY MISSION TO PUT
YOU IN PRISON AS AN ACCESSORY.

12:57.940 --> 13:00.101
NICE SPIKER.

13:01.210 --> 13:03.303
DIG IT OUT, BABY.
DIG IT OUT.

13:03.350 --> 13:04.544
MAKE DADDY PROUD.

13:04.580 --> 13:06.502
HEY, LISTEN, I NEED YOU
TO DO ME A FAVOR.

13:06.550 --> 13:09.747
IT'S NOT THAT FAVOR BOBBY BROWN
DOES FOR WHITNEY, IS IT?

13:09.780 --> 13:10.610
NO.

13:10.650 --> 13:12.311
YEAH, THEN, WHAT UP?

13:12.350 --> 13:15.251
I NEED YOU TO TRY TO BUY SOME
ECSTASY FROM A COUPLE P.C.H.ers.

13:15.290 --> 13:18.555
YEAH, NO SWEAT.
I'M LIKE THIS WITH THOSE GUYS.

13:20.200 --> 13:23.328
OH, NO, HONEY,
BAD SET, BAD SET.

13:23.370 --> 13:26.498
DON'T MAKE DADDY
HOSE YOU DOWN.

13:26.530 --> 13:29.909
YOU'RE NOT REAL COMPLICATED,
ARE YOU, DICK?

13:29.940 --> 13:31.532
I TRY NOT TO BE.

13:35.480 --> 13:37.175
THAT'S EVERYTHING.

13:40.250 --> 13:41.911
BE'I'I'ER BE.

13:46.490 --> 13:50.358
WAITING FOR YOUR GIRLFRIEND
TO MAKE BAIL?

13:50.390 --> 13:51.459
NO, NO, NO.

13:51.490 --> 13:53.299
HER SHIFI' ENDS AT 5:00.

13:53.330 --> 13:56.322
I'M WAITING FOR YOU,
V-DOG.

13:56.360 --> 13:57.896
WHAT FOR?

13:57.930 --> 14:00.490
I THOUGHT MAYBE YOU'D TELL ME
WHERE YOU'RE KEEPING DUNCAN,

14:00.540 --> 14:03.031
SAVE US ALL SOME TIME, YOU KNOW,
EARN SOME KARMA POINTS.

14:03.070 --> 14:05.209
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHERE HE IS,

14:05.240 --> 14:08.004
AND IF I DID,
YOU WOULD BE THE...

14:08.040 --> 14:09.473
LAST PERSON I'D TELL.

14:09.510 --> 14:11.000
AM I HEARING YOU RIGHT?

14:11.050 --> 14:13.143
YOU'D TELL OSAMA BIN LADEN
BEFORE YOU'D TELL ME?

14:13.180 --> 14:14.545
BECAUSE BACK IN MY DAY,

14:14.580 --> 14:16.343
WE HAD A LITTLE THING
CALLED PATRIOTISM.

14:16.380 --> 14:19.417
HOLD ON. HOLD ON. HOLD ON.
IT'S A NEGOTIATION, RIGHT?

14:19.450 --> 14:23.523
LET'S SAY I SWEETEN THE POT.
LET'S MAKE IT...

14:23.560 --> 14:24.822
$5,000.

14:24.860 --> 14:26.418
THE KARMA POINTS
ARE YOURS TO KEEP,

14:26.460 --> 14:30.066
AND IF YOU ACT NOW, I'LL THROW
IN A FREE SET OF STEAK KNIVES.

14:30.100 --> 14:33.069
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE HE IS.

14:33.100 --> 14:35.330
ALL RIGHT, SAY NO MORE.
I GAVE IT A SHOT.

14:35.370 --> 14:37.600
YOU CAN'T
BLAME A GUY FOR THAT.

14:39.110 --> 14:41.476
HEY, VINNIE...

14:41.510 --> 14:45.207
YOU DROPPED
YOUR PEN IN MY BAG.

14:45.250 --> 14:46.842
YOU SURE IT'S MINE?

14:46.880 --> 14:48.518
I DON'T THINK
I'M MISSING A PEN.

14:48.550 --> 14:54.557
"SUGARS CABARET INVITATIONAL
LONG BALL CHAMPIONSHIP."

14:59.730 --> 15:01.618
PRETTY SURE IT'S YOURS.

15:07.140 --> 15:11.429
VERONICA, 72 HOURS FROM NOW,
I'M GONNA HAVE THAT KID BACK,

15:11.470 --> 15:14.303
AND YOU'LL WISH
YOU HAD THOSE STEAK KNIVES.

15:23.550 --> 15:27.657
NEXT QUESTION
IN THE SEARCH-ENGINE OLYMPICS.

15:27.690 --> 15:29.555
CONTESTANTS, GET READY.

15:29.590 --> 15:34.459
WHAT IS THE VARSITY
BOYS' BASKETBALL TEAM'S RECORD

15:34.500 --> 15:36.297
IN DISTRICT PLAY?

15:36.330 --> 15:38.890
GO!

15:38.930 --> 15:40.238
Veronica: I KILL IN THIS GAME.

15:40.270 --> 15:41.760
SEE, WHILE MY NIMROD CLASSMATES

15:41.800 --> 15:44.030
ARE TYPING IN
"NEPTUNE HIGH BASKETBALL"

15:44.070 --> 15:45.537
AND GETTING 50 PAGES
OF RESULTS,

15:45.570 --> 15:48.209
ALL I HAVE TO DO
IS TYPE IN WALLACE'S NAME,

15:48.240 --> 15:50.902
THEN CLICK THE MOST RECENT
BOX SCORE, THEN --

15:50.950 --> 15:53.669
BOX SCORES FROM CHICAGO?

15:53.720 --> 15:55.415
WALLACE LIED.

15:55.450 --> 15:57.748
HE DIDN'T COME BACK TO NEPTUNE
TO PLAY BASKETBALL.

15:57.790 --> 15:59.280
BY THE LOOKS OF THIS,

15:59.320 --> 16:03.279
HE WAS HAVING A DREAM SEASON
IN CHICAGO.

16:04.160 --> 16:05.752
HEY, WHAT'S THE WORD?

16:05.790 --> 16:08.293
THE ONE THEY CALL BOOTSY TOLD ME
NO AND WENT ON TO SUGGEST

16:08.330 --> 16:10.821
I PERFORM SEXUAL INTERCOURSE
UPON MY OWN PERSON.

16:10.870 --> 16:12.269
DOESN'T HE UNDERSTAND?

16:12.300 --> 16:14.666
IF YOU COULD DO THAT,
YOU'D NEVER COME TO SCHOOL.

16:14.700 --> 16:16.167
BOY, THAT'S THE TRUTH.

16:16.200 --> 16:17.929
THEN AFTER?

16:17.970 --> 16:20.177
SOLD ME 10 HITS OF "E."
MINT?

16:20.210 --> 16:22.371
I GAVE YOU ENOUGH CASH
FOR 20.

16:22.410 --> 16:26.005
HE GAVE ME THE 09er DISCOUNT,
CHARGED ME DOUBLE.

16:26.050 --> 16:28.575
AND YOU PAID IT?
WHAT'S TIME TO A HOG?

16:41.660 --> 16:44.094
OFF ME, BOY.

16:55.240 --> 16:58.073
WE'D LIKE TO CONSIDER
SCALING THE SEARCHES BACK.

16:58.110 --> 16:59.668
NO, I DON'T THINK
HE'S LEFT TOWN YET.

16:59.710 --> 17:02.440
IT'S REALLY A ZOO DOWN HERE.
IF YOU COULD SEE IT --

17:02.480 --> 17:04.812
I UNDERSTAND PERFECT LY WHAT THIS
IS DOING AT THE BORDER CROSSING.

17:04.850 --> 17:07.557
But I'll tell you what --
let me think about it.

17:09.660 --> 17:13.756
Woman: Clear.
88-14, clear.

17:18.200 --> 17:20.691
YOU'VE GOT COMPANY.

17:20.740 --> 17:22.059
NOT NOW.

17:22.100 --> 17:24.159
IT'S THE FBI.

17:26.210 --> 17:28.838
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
GET BACK TO YOU.

17:28.880 --> 17:30.575
YES. BYE.

17:32.110 --> 17:34.442
SEND THEM IN.

17:43.890 --> 17:46.825
RIGHT IN HERE.

17:53.540 --> 17:54.734
SHERIFF?

17:57.140 --> 17:58.562
OH.

18:00.680 --> 18:03.035
AGENT MORRIS.
AGENT WILLS.

18:03.080 --> 18:04.274
SHERIFF DON LAMB.

18:04.310 --> 18:06.676
TAKE YOURSELVES A SEAT.
THANK YOU.

18:08.880 --> 18:11.610
SHERIFF, I THINK WE SHOULD MAKE
IT CLEAR RIGHT FROM THE GET-GO

18:11.650 --> 18:13.459
THAT WE ARE HERE
TO GET THAT BABY BACK,

18:13.490 --> 18:16.357
AND WE ARE WILLING
TO COMBINE OUR RESOURCES...

18:16.390 --> 18:17.721
I'LL SHARE ANYTHING
THAT YOU NEED --

18:17.760 --> 18:19.648
...UNTIL SUCH TIME
AS YOU PISS US OFF.

18:19.690 --> 18:21.658
AND WHEN
THAT TIME COMES --

18:21.700 --> 18:23.827
AND IT USUALLY COMES QUICKLY
IN SLEEPYBURG

18:23.870 --> 18:25.895
OR "WORLD'S BIGGEST
BALL OF STRINGSVILLE"

18:25.930 --> 18:28.865
OR WHEREVER THE HELL WE ARE THIS
WEEK -- WHEN THAT TIME COMES,

18:28.900 --> 18:31.437
WE WILL CUT YOU OUT
LIKE YOU WERE A METER MAID.

18:31.470 --> 18:33.734
YOU DON'T GET
THE PHOTO OP,

18:33.780 --> 18:36.908
AND YOU DON'T GET
THE FRUIT BASKET.

18:36.940 --> 18:38.669
SO, REPEAT AFTER ME.

18:39.950 --> 18:42.168
TEAM.

18:43.080 --> 18:44.581
ME.

18:45.890 --> 18:47.710
TEAM.

18:48.620 --> 18:51.157
COME ON,
YOU CAN DO IT.

18:51.190 --> 18:52.919
TEAM.

18:52.960 --> 18:54.848
ME.

18:54.900 --> 18:56.049
ME.

18:56.100 --> 18:57.397
GREAT.

18:57.430 --> 18:58.727
SO, WHY DON'T YOU
GET US UP TO SPEED

18:58.770 --> 19:01.193
WITH WHAT YOU'VE
BEEN DOING HERE.

19:04.770 --> 19:07.102
Veronica:
IS THE SHERIFF AROUND?

19:07.140 --> 19:08.277
HE'S IN WITH THE FBI.

19:08.310 --> 19:09.834
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:09.880 --> 19:11.939
YOU'RE VERONICA MARS,
AREN'T YOU?

19:11.980 --> 19:13.413
THAT'S ME.

19:13.450 --> 19:15.509
I'M SUPPOSED TO
KEEP AN EYE ON YOU.

19:15.550 --> 19:16.847
GREAT.

19:22.520 --> 19:24.181
YOU EVER HIT THE CLUBS
IN L.A.?

19:24.230 --> 19:25.720
I'M 18.

19:25.760 --> 19:27.625
YEAH, SHOW ME A CLUB
THAT'LL CARE.

19:27.660 --> 19:29.628
I MOONLIGHT
OVER AT CLUB THIN.

19:29.660 --> 19:30.866
CLUB THIN?

19:30.900 --> 19:32.162
I'M A BOUNCER.

19:32.200 --> 19:33.736
I DIDN'T THINK
YOU WERE A CAGE DANCER.

19:33.770 --> 19:37.809
THE REASON WHY I ASK --
YOU COME UP, I'LL GET YOU IN.

19:37.840 --> 19:38.864
OKAY.

19:38.910 --> 19:40.309
COOL.

19:40.340 --> 19:41.898
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

19:41.940 --> 19:43.339
YES?

19:43.380 --> 19:45.871
SHERIFF, VERONICA MARS
IS LOOKING FOR YOU.

19:45.910 --> 19:48.515
SHE SAYS SHE HAS SOMETHING
YOU MIGHT BE INTERESTED IN.

19:48.550 --> 19:50.211
MARS?
YOU MEAN THE GIRLFRIEND?

19:50.250 --> 19:51.649
PUT HER IN INTERROGATION.

19:51.690 --> 19:53.487
EX-GIRLFRIEND, UGLY BREAKUP,
FROM WHAT I HEARD.

19:53.520 --> 19:54.987
BEFORE WE GO IN THERE,

19:55.020 --> 19:56.749
YOU SHOULD PROBABLY KNOW
SOMETHING ABOUT VERONICA MARS.

19:56.790 --> 19:59.258
WE NEED TO BE CAREFUL
WITH THIS ONE.

19:59.290 --> 20:01.622
SHE'S SLIPPERY.

20:03.600 --> 20:06.922
SHERIFF, WE HAVE INTERROGATED
AL QAEDA MEMBERS AT GITMO.

20:06.970 --> 20:10.269
I THINK WE CAN HANDLE
A TEENAGE GIRL.

20:15.380 --> 20:17.746
NICK AND JESSICA.

20:17.780 --> 20:19.577
IS NOTHING SACRED?

20:19.610 --> 20:22.317
WHOA, AGENT WILLS,
CALL FOR BACKUP.

20:22.350 --> 20:24.784
JUST THE CHOPPER?
SNIPERS.

20:27.520 --> 20:30.011
WHAT IS IT, VERONICA?

20:30.060 --> 20:32.528
WHO ARE THE SUITS?

20:32.560 --> 20:35.358
AGENT MORRIS, AGENT WILLS --
THEY'RE WITH THE FBI.

20:35.400 --> 20:36.651
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

20:36.700 --> 20:38.691
DUNCAN MAY HAVE TAKEN
HIS COMPUTER,

20:38.730 --> 20:40.459
BUT HE HAD
A .MAC ACCOUNT.

20:40.500 --> 20:42.434
HE USED IT
TO BACK UP HIS LAPTOP.

20:42.470 --> 20:44.438
WHAT'S A .MAC?
ONLINE STORAGE.

20:44.470 --> 20:46.461
USERS CAN
BACK UP THEIR FILES OR --

20:46.510 --> 20:49.502
SYNCHRONIZE THEIR COMPUTERS,
CALENDARS, ADDRESSES.

20:49.540 --> 20:50.905
BROWSER BOOKMARKS.

20:50.950 --> 20:52.372
IT WASN'T ON YOUR LIST?

20:52.410 --> 20:54.617
I JUST THOUGHT OF IT,
AND I CAME STRAIGHT HERE.

20:54.650 --> 20:57.016
I CAN GET A WARRANT
SO WE CAN SEARCH IT.

20:57.050 --> 21:00.486
YEAH, GET THE COMPUTER BOYS
TO BREAK THE PASSWORD.

21:00.520 --> 21:01.817
BORDER PATROL ON LINE ONE.

21:01.860 --> 21:04.249
BORDER PATROL?
DON'T BOTH ER.

21:04.290 --> 21:05.951
DUNCAN HATES MEXICO.

21:05.990 --> 21:08.993
IS THAT SO, BRER RABBIT?

21:09.030 --> 21:10.918
YEAH, THIS IS LAMB.

21:10.970 --> 21:13.097
NO, DON'T BACK OFF
THOSE SEARCHES AT ALL.

21:13.130 --> 21:14.631
NO, NOT AT ALL.

21:14.670 --> 21:18.106
VERONICA, WHY DON'T YOU WAIT
OUTSIDE IN THE HALL?

21:18.140 --> 21:20.199
WHY DON'T YOU?

21:20.240 --> 21:22.003
YOUR NEXT OPTION
IS A CELL.

21:28.880 --> 21:32.043
WE'LL TAKE A COFFEE
WHEN YOU GET A MINUTE.

21:34.560 --> 21:37.381
SACKS, TWO COFFEES.

21:39.830 --> 21:43.322
SO...

21:43.370 --> 21:45.326
THE FBI.

21:45.370 --> 21:48.259
I'VE THOUGHT ABOUT IT,
YOU KNOW?

21:48.300 --> 21:51.531
BUT BIG FISH, SMALL TOWN
HAS ITS PERKS.

21:51.570 --> 21:54.437
STILL, WHO KNOWS?
I STILL MIGHT APPLY.

21:54.480 --> 21:55.936
YOU GO TO COLLEGE?

21:55.980 --> 21:57.470
FOR A YEAR.

21:57.510 --> 21:59.148
BLEW OUT A KNEE AT
SOUTHWEST TEXAS PLAYING BALL.

21:59.180 --> 22:00.477
SPEAK A FOREIGN LANGUAGE?

22:00.520 --> 22:02.545
A LITTLE MEXICAN,
ENOUGH TO GET BY.

22:02.580 --> 22:03.979
I TELL THEM
TO TURN THEIR MUSIC DOWN.

22:04.020 --> 22:06.580
ANY EXPERTISE IN
COMPUTER SCIENCE, LAW,

22:06.620 --> 22:09.350
PHYSICS, CHEMISTRY,
FORENSICS, MATHEMATICS?

22:09.390 --> 22:12.223
EXPERTISE?

22:12.260 --> 22:13.796
SMALL TOWN, BIG FISH --

22:13.830 --> 22:16.958
YOU KNOW,
I'D RIDE WITH THAT.

22:22.200 --> 22:24.760
Hector: I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'RE
TALKING ABOUT, WEEVIL.

22:24.810 --> 22:27.404
I'M NOT IN BUSINESS
WITH THE FITZPATRICKS.

22:27.440 --> 22:28.998
I KNOW YOU'RE LYING,
HECTOR.

22:29.040 --> 22:32.146
I KNOW YOU SOLD "E" TO AN 09er
JUST TODAY.

22:32.180 --> 22:33.147
THAT?

22:33.180 --> 22:34.272
YEAH, THAT.

22:34.320 --> 22:36.880
YOU DID IT,
DIDN'T YOU?

22:36.920 --> 22:38.911
YEAH, BUT I DIDN'T GET IT
FROM THE FITZPATRICKS.

22:38.950 --> 22:41.384
SOME WHITE BOY
ASKED ME TO GET HIM SOME.

22:41.420 --> 22:42.785
HE LOOKED DUMB
AND DESPERATE,

22:42.820 --> 22:45.357
SO I SAID I'D GET IT FOR HIM
AT $40 A HIT.

22:45.390 --> 22:47.221
HE SAID YEAH, SO...
SO WHAT?

22:47.260 --> 22:51.026
SO I GOT IT FROM THIS OTHER
WHITE BOY WHO I KNOW DEALS.

22:51.070 --> 22:52.469
HE'S LYING.

22:52.500 --> 22:53.569
WHAT WHITE BOY?

22:53.600 --> 22:55.192
WHAT WAS SO WRONG?

22:55.240 --> 22:58.698
I MADE A FEW BUCKS SELLING
FROM ONE 09er TO ANOTHER.

22:58.740 --> 23:01.277
COME ON. LIKE YOU KNOW
AN 09er DRUG DEALER?

23:01.310 --> 23:02.572
WHO WAS IT?

23:02.610 --> 23:04.271
MY SISTER
WORKS WITH HIS DAD.

23:04.310 --> 23:06.847
I WANT A NAME.

23:07.950 --> 23:11.317
VERONICA,
THEY GOT INTO THE FILES.

23:11.350 --> 23:12.886
WE NEED YOU.

23:15.920 --> 23:17.478
THAT WAS QUICK.

23:17.530 --> 23:19.350
TWO HOURS
FOR THE SEARCH WARRANT,

23:19.390 --> 23:20.823
10 MINUTES
TO BREAK HIS PASSWORD.

23:20.860 --> 23:23.693
WHAT WAS IT?
ENAK GEM.

23:23.730 --> 23:26.494
WHAT?
WHAT'S SHE GONNA DO WITH IT?

23:26.530 --> 23:28.191
ENAK GEM?

23:28.240 --> 23:30.094
"MEG KANE" BACKWARDS.

23:30.140 --> 23:31.630
MISS MARS,

23:31.670 --> 23:34.730
WHAT CAN YOU TELL US ABOUT
DUNCAN KANE'S SAILING ABILITY?

23:34.780 --> 23:37.237
DUNCAN'S BEEN SAILING
HIS WHOLE LIFE. WHY?

23:37.280 --> 23:40.249
DUNCAN BOOKMARKED A BOAT.
WE TRACKED DOWN THE SELLER.

23:40.280 --> 23:44.080
TURNS OUT HE SOLD IT LAST WEEK
TO A TEENAGE BOY WHO PAID CASH.

23:44.120 --> 23:46.987
I ASSUME THAT'S A GENEROUS USE
OF THE TERM "WE"?

23:47.020 --> 23:49.159
I GOT A HUNDRED BUCKS
SAYS HE'S HEADING SOUTH.

23:49.190 --> 23:52.159
WHAT DO YOU THINK? WANT TO PUT
YOUR MONEY WHERE YOUR MOUTH IS?

23:52.190 --> 23:55.398
HOW MUCH DOES YOUR BOYFRIEND
HATE MEXICO, HUH?

23:55.430 --> 23:57.193
ISN'T GAMBLING ILLEGAL?

23:57.230 --> 23:58.959
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

23:59.000 --> 24:01.935
IT'S THE COAST GUARD.
THEY SPOTTED THE BOAT.

24:01.970 --> 24:03.608
IT'S IGNORING
THEIR WARNING CALLS.

24:03.640 --> 24:05.858
THEY'RE PREPARING
TO BOARD.

24:05.910 --> 24:07.730
THAT KID'S
GONNA GET HIMSELF KILLED.

24:07.780 --> 24:09.372
PUT IT ON THE SPEAKER.

24:10.040 --> 24:14.511
Man: There's no_one on deck.
Our men are checking down below.

24:19.150 --> 24:20.447
No one on board.

24:20.490 --> 24:22.708
But we have found dirty diapers

24:22.760 --> 24:25.627
and 12 empty cans
of Spaghettios.

24:25.660 --> 24:28.049
WHAT ABOUT HISTORY
OF MENTAL ISSUES?

24:28.100 --> 24:31.866
ANY CHANCE THAT HE JUST SAID,
"GOODBYE, CRUEL WORLD"?

24:31.900 --> 24:35.233
DUNCAN DIDN'T KILL HIMSELF,
AND HE DIDN'T KILL HIS BABY.

24:35.270 --> 24:37.465
SOMEBODY PICKED HIM UP.

24:37.510 --> 24:40.001
HE'S STILL ON THE RUN.

25:09.970 --> 25:11.198
MORNING, SAM.

25:11.240 --> 25:14.129
MORNING, RALPH.

25:15.580 --> 25:16.899
FRITTER?

25:16.940 --> 25:19.602
YOU SHOULD BE OUT
LOOKING FOR DUNCAN.

25:20.850 --> 25:24.889
OH, RIGHT!
DUNCAN KANE.

25:24.920 --> 25:25.989
AAAH!

25:26.020 --> 25:27.783
I GOT SO SWEPT UP
IN YOUR BEAUTY,

25:27.820 --> 25:29.253
I ALMOST FORGOT
MY ASSIGNMENT.

25:29.290 --> 25:33.181
IF YOU DO FIND HIM
AND HE GIVES YOU ANY TROUBLE,

25:33.230 --> 25:35.152
WILL YOU GIVE HIM THIS?

25:38.700 --> 25:40.668
WILL DO.

25:50.980 --> 25:54.518
OH, HOW THE MIGHTY
HAVE FALLEN.

25:54.550 --> 25:57.417
DO YOU REMEMBER LAST YEAR
WHEN YOU LOOKED DOWN ON ME

25:57.450 --> 25:59.213
LIKE YOU
WERE SO MUCH BETTER?

25:59.250 --> 26:03.414
YEAH. DID YOU GET THE IMPRESSION
SOMETHING HAS CHANGED?

26:03.460 --> 26:04.620
WELL, YEAH.

26:04.660 --> 26:06.218
IT SEEMS
BOTH OUR FAMILIES

26:06.260 --> 26:08.990
ARE IN THE
DOMESTIC STAFFING INDUSTRY.

26:09.030 --> 26:12.568
THAT MAKES US
LIKE FAMILY.

26:12.600 --> 26:14.090
I STEAL CARS.
YOU SELL DRUGS.

26:14.140 --> 26:16.700
HEY, I CAN HARDLY TELL
WHERE YOU END AND I BEGIN.

26:16.740 --> 26:18.560
I GET IT.

26:18.610 --> 26:19.907
WHAT CAN I GET YOU?

26:19.940 --> 26:23.000
A LITTLE CRANK,
SOME BLOW?

26:23.040 --> 26:25.008
JUST TELL ME
THE NAME OF YOUR SUPPLIER.

26:25.050 --> 26:26.847
YEAH,
THAT'S NOT HAPPENING.

26:26.880 --> 26:28.279
IS IT THE FITZPATRICKS?

26:28.320 --> 26:29.810
THE FITZPATRICKS?

26:29.850 --> 26:33.854
THEY TAKE A BLOWTORCH TO YOU
IF YOU'RE SHORT A DIME BAG.

26:34.790 --> 26:36.655
I'M NOT THAT DUMB.

26:38.790 --> 26:42.453
AM I FREE TO GO?

26:42.500 --> 26:44.889
HAVE A NICE DAY.

26:52.170 --> 26:55.037
YOU BELIEVE HIM?

26:55.080 --> 26:56.604
DON'T YOU?

26:57.710 --> 27:01.419
ONE OF MY BOYS IS MIXED UP WITH
THE FITZPATRICKS. I KNOW IT.

27:01.450 --> 27:02.872
HAS IT CROSSED YOUR MIND

27:02.920 --> 27:04.945
THAT MAYBE THE ONE
MIXED UP WITH THE FITZPATRICKS

27:04.990 --> 27:06.480
IS THE ONE
THAT'S ALREADY DEAD?

27:06.520 --> 27:08.954
YOU REMEMBER WHEN KAREN
AND PATRICK FITZPATRICK

27:08.990 --> 27:12.050
STILL WENT TO SCHOOL HERE
BACK WHEN WE WERE FRESHMAN?

27:12.090 --> 27:14.229
THEY WERE LIKE
SEVENTH-YEAR SENIORS.

27:14.260 --> 27:15.921
THE ONLY REASON
THEY STUCK AROUND

27:15.960 --> 27:17.427
WAS TO KEEP THE HIGH-SCHOOL
DRUG TRADE GOING.

27:17.460 --> 27:19.496
AS SOON AS THIS SCHOOL GOT SMART
AND EXPELLED THEM,

27:19.530 --> 27:20.792
MY PREDECESSOR --

27:20.840 --> 27:22.467
THE REAPER, GUS.

27:22.500 --> 27:24.968
YES, THE REAPER --
DECIDED TO EXPAND OUR BUSINESS.

27:25.010 --> 27:27.899
A COUPLE MONTHS IN,
HE DISAPPEARS LIKE JIMMY HOFFA.

27:27.940 --> 27:29.601
NO ONE'S SEEN HIM SINCE.

27:29.640 --> 27:32.643
YOU KNOW WHY THE REAPER
WAS CALLED THAT?
HE LOST A BET?

27:32.680 --> 27:34.671
HIS NAME --
GUSTAVIO TOOM BS.

27:34.720 --> 27:36.369
HE WAS FELIX'S BIG BROTHER.

27:36.420 --> 27:40.140
SO, NO, FELIX WASN'T
WORKING WITH THE FITZPATRICKS,

27:40.190 --> 27:41.782
NO WAY IN HELL.

27:52.400 --> 27:54.197
GONNA EAT YOUR CAKE?

27:54.240 --> 27:56.060
TAKE IT.

27:56.100 --> 27:59.103
I GOT A LITTLE PRESENT
FOR YOU.

27:59.140 --> 28:01.370
WHAT IS IT?

28:01.410 --> 28:03.901
JUST A LITTLE SCRAPBOOK
I PUT TOGETHER.

28:03.950 --> 28:06.601
YOU WERE KICKING BUTT
IN CHICAGO --

28:06.650 --> 28:09.369
8 POINTS,
11 ASSISTS A GAME?

28:09.420 --> 28:10.478
UNDEFEATED?

28:10.520 --> 28:12.886
I WANTED TO TELL YOU.

28:12.920 --> 28:14.979
WHY DID YOU REALLY COME BACK,
WALLACE?

28:15.020 --> 28:16.487
IF YOU READ THESE STORIES,

28:16.520 --> 28:18.249
THEN YOU KNOW MY NEW TEAMMATE
WAS RASHARD RUCKER.

28:18.290 --> 28:20.326
IS THAT SUPPOSED TO
MEAN SOMETHING?
YEAH.

28:20.360 --> 28:22.499
HE'S THE BEST HIGH SCHOOL PLAYER
IN THE NATION,

28:22.530 --> 28:24.225
THIS YEAR'S
LEBRON JAM ES.

28:24.270 --> 28:26.898
JUST BEFORE CHRISTMAS,
ME AND RASHARD,

28:26.930 --> 28:30.388
A COUPLE OF GUYS ON THE TEAM,
HIT THIS HOUSE PARTY.

28:30.440 --> 28:34.501
RASHARD HAD A FEW BEERS, BUT
HE SAID HE WAS OKAY TO DRIVE.

28:34.540 --> 28:36.735
ON THE WAY HOME,

28:36.780 --> 28:38.771
THIS WINO STAGGERED OUT
IN FRONT OF THE CAR.

28:38.810 --> 28:40.277
OH, WALLACE.

28:40.310 --> 28:42.039
HE HIT HIM.

28:42.080 --> 28:45.049
I WAS YELLING FOR HIM TO STOP,
BUT HE PANICKED.

28:45.090 --> 28:46.819
WE DROVE
TO HIS UNCLE'S.

28:46.850 --> 28:48.613
HIS UNCLE'S?

28:48.660 --> 28:50.753
HE'S RASHARD'S AGENT,
MANAGER, BOSS.

28:50.790 --> 28:52.428
HE SAID
WE PROBABLY HIT A DOG

28:52.460 --> 28:54.690
AND WE SHOULD JUST
KEEP OUR MOUTHS SHUT.

28:54.730 --> 28:56.618
"MILLIONS OF DOLLARS
ARE AT STAKE."

28:56.660 --> 28:59.060
BUT I COULDN'T
JUST LET IT GO.

29:00.730 --> 29:05.167
I COULDN'T GO TO PRACTICE AND
JUST PRETEND IT HADN'T HAPPENED.

29:05.210 --> 29:07.269
SO, I THOUGHT
IF I CAME BACK HERE,

29:07.310 --> 29:09.232
I COULD JUST
FORGET ABOUT IT.

29:09.280 --> 29:11.009
YOU KNOW,
YOU COULD HAVE TOLD ME.

29:11.050 --> 29:12.677
NO, I COULDN'T.
WHY?

29:12.710 --> 29:16.510
BECAUSE YOU WOULD'VE STAYED.
YOU'D HAVE DONE THE RIGHT THING.

29:17.580 --> 29:19.741
I'M EMBARRASSED I DIDN'T.

29:19.790 --> 29:21.849
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

29:21.890 --> 29:23.016
HELLO?

29:23.060 --> 29:24.379
Duncan:
Veronica, It's me.

29:24.430 --> 29:25.783
DUNCAN, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
WHERE ARE YOU?

29:25.830 --> 29:27.422
YOU GOT TO
TURN YOURSELF IN.

29:27.460 --> 29:29.894
Where I am isn't important.
I'm doing the right thing.

29:29.930 --> 29:32.467
NO, YOU'RE NOT.
YOU NEED TO TURN YOURSELF IN.

29:32.500 --> 29:34.934
YOU'RE NOT READY
TO RAISE THAT BABY.

29:34.970 --> 29:36.039
WE'LL WIN IN COURT.

29:36.070 --> 29:37.435
There's no way
I'll ever...

29:37.470 --> 29:39.529
DON'T HANG UP.
TELL ME WHERE YOU ARE.

29:39.570 --> 29:40.969
I thought you'd help.

29:41.010 --> 29:43.570
DUNCAN, YOU'RE GONNA GET
YOURSELF THROWN IN PRISON.

29:43.610 --> 29:44.941
THEY THINK I HELPED YOU.

29:44.980 --> 29:48.108
[ Dial tone ]

29:50.550 --> 29:51.983
Agent Morris: GOT IT?

29:52.020 --> 29:55.808
HE'S UP IN BIG BEAR.
JUST GIVE ME FIVE MINUTES.

29:55.860 --> 29:57.828
I'LL HAVE IT DOWN
TO A BUILDING.

29:57.860 --> 29:59.487
WE CAN BE THERE
IN TWO HOURS.

29:59.530 --> 30:01.498
SHERIFF, WE APPRECIATE
YOUR TIME, YOUR EFFORT,

30:01.530 --> 30:05.364
AND YOUR COOPERATION,
BUT WE GOT IT.

30:32.460 --> 30:34.553
IT'S TIME.

30:43.140 --> 30:45.631
DUNCAN,
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

30:45.670 --> 30:47.103
I KNOW.

30:47.140 --> 30:50.837
WE'RE DOING
THE RIGHT THING.
I THINK SO.

30:55.080 --> 30:56.638
YOU READY TO TRAVEL?

30:56.680 --> 31:00.309
READY FOR A BIG TRIP?

31:01.490 --> 31:04.755
THE FBI IS HEADING UP
TO BIG BEAR. WE GOT TO MOVE.

31:04.790 --> 31:06.883
KENDALL?

31:06.930 --> 31:10.252
EVERYONE BOUGHT IT,
INCLUDING HER.

31:10.300 --> 31:12.598
THE BOAT?
THE SAME.

31:12.630 --> 31:14.097
EVERYTHING'S IN MOTION.

31:14.140 --> 31:16.290
WE GOT TO GO NOW,
OR THINGS ARE GONNA FALL APART.

31:16.340 --> 31:18.399
VERONICA,
SLOW DOWN ONE MINUTE.

31:18.440 --> 31:20.863
AFTER WE LEAVE THIS ROOM,
WE CAN'T CALL EACH OTHER,

31:20.910 --> 31:22.901
E-MAIL EACH OTHER,
SEE EACH OTHER --

31:22.940 --> 31:24.544
STOP.

31:26.910 --> 31:28.309
GOODBYE, VERONICA.

31:28.350 --> 31:31.080
I LOVE YOU.

31:31.120 --> 31:34.886
ALWAYS HAVE,
ALWAYS WILL.

31:37.060 --> 31:38.948
YOU BETTER.

31:43.160 --> 31:45.219
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
SHERIFF.

31:45.270 --> 31:46.328
YEAH?

31:46.370 --> 31:48.361
WE GOT A HIT
ON VERONICA'S ATM CARD.

31:48.400 --> 31:49.936
WHERE?

31:49.970 --> 31:53.133
MEXICO, A HOTEL NEAR JACUMBA.
IT'S BIG WITH AMERICAN SURFERS.

31:56.680 --> 31:58.079
I TOLD THEM, DIDN'T I?

31:58.110 --> 32:01.273
EVERYTHING OUT OF
THAT GIRL'S MOUTH IS A LIE.

32:01.320 --> 32:02.912
LET'S SEE
HOW THE FBI LIKES IT

32:02.950 --> 32:05.043
WHEN THIS HIGH-SCHOOLâ€”EDUCATED
LOCAL LAWMAN

32:05.090 --> 32:07.149
BRINGS BACK THE PRIZE.

32:56.000 --> 32:57.968
[ PHONE DIALING ]

32:58.010 --> 33:00.365
[ PHONE RINGING ]

33:10.820 --> 33:14.916
Veronica: IT'S VERONICA.
LEAVE A MESSAGE.

33:14.960 --> 33:16.552
VERONICA...

33:16.590 --> 33:19.957
HEY, I NEED TO SEE YOU AT HOME
A.S.A.P., KIDDO.

33:19.990 --> 33:23.153
WE NEED A LITTLE
DADDY-DAUGHTER TIME.

33:28.500 --> 33:30.934
HE KNOWS YOU CAN SHOOT,
JUST LIKE I KNOW YOU CAN SHOOT.

33:30.970 --> 33:32.403
WALLACE FENNEL?

33:32.440 --> 33:33.737
YEAH.

33:33.770 --> 33:35.374
ERNIE SAYERS,
CHICAGO STATESMAN.

33:35.410 --> 33:38.208
I WAS HOPING
TO ASK YOU A FEW QUESTIONS.

33:39.180 --> 33:40.647
THE NIGHT
OF DECEMBER 14th,

33:40.680 --> 33:42.841
A HOMELESS MAN WAS THE VICTIM
OF A HIT-AND-RUN.

33:42.880 --> 33:45.246
YOU MIND?

33:45.290 --> 33:48.885
THAT MAN IS PARALYZED
FROM THE WAIST DOWN.

33:48.920 --> 33:51.957
NOW, A CONVENIENCE-STORE CLERK
WHO WAS LOCKING UP

33:51.990 --> 33:53.719
SAYS THAT
THE CAR THAT HIT HIM

33:53.760 --> 33:56.297
WAS A RED HUMMER
WITH 22-INCH SPINNING RIMS.

33:56.330 --> 33:59.766
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY OF THOSE
THERE ARE IN CHICAGO?

33:59.800 --> 34:01.665
LESS THAN YOU'D THINK.

34:01.700 --> 34:03.691
I TALKED TO SOME KIDS
FROM YOUR OLD SCHOOL.

34:03.740 --> 34:05.765
THEY SAID THAT YOU,
RASHARD RUCKER,

34:05.810 --> 34:07.209
AND A COUPLE OF TEAMMATES

34:07.240 --> 34:09.037
LEFT A HOUSE PARTY
AROUND 2:00 AM. THAT NIGHT.

34:09.080 --> 34:10.809
SO, WHAT'S THE QUESTION?

34:10.840 --> 34:12.273
I GUESS THE QUESTION IS,

34:12.310 --> 34:15.143
WHAT KIND OF MAN
WERE YOU PLANNING ON BEING?

34:18.250 --> 34:21.651
[ OLD 97's "FOUR LEAF CLOVER"
PLAYS ]

34:41.280 --> 34:45.444
* I GOT A FOUR LEAF CLOVER

34:45.480 --> 34:49.814
* IT AIN'T DONE
ONE SINGLE LICK OF GOOD *

34:49.850 --> 34:53.411
* I'M STILL A DRUNK,
I'M STILL A LOSER *

34:53.450 --> 34:58.126
* LIVING IN
A LOUSY NEIGHBORHOOD *

34:58.160 --> 34:59.821
* WHY DON'T YOU COME OVER?

34:59.860 --> 35:01.589
* I'LL SHOW YOU
MY FOUR LEAF CLOVER *

35:01.630 --> 35:03.222
* WHO AM I TRYING TO KID?

35:03.260 --> 35:07.492
* I'M NOT THE KIND OF GUY
YOU'D GO FOR *

35:07.530 --> 35:11.705
* I GOT A FOUR LEAF CLOVER

35:11.740 --> 35:17.133
* BUT I AIN'T GOT NO HOPE
OF GETTING YOU *

35:31.990 --> 35:33.753
USTED LO HA VISTO?

35:33.790 --> 35:35.052
NO.

35:35.100 --> 35:37.591
BUT YOU ALL
LOOK ALIKE TO ME.

35:39.230 --> 35:43.360
TRY THE RESTAURANT
UP THE ROAD.

35:47.010 --> 35:48.705
IF THEY TAKE YOU AWAY,

35:48.740 --> 35:51.208
IF YOU'RE
SENT TO PRISON --

35:51.250 --> 35:53.639
YOU READ THE LETTERS,
THOUGH, RIGHT?

35:53.680 --> 35:56.217
FROM MEG TO
CHILD PROTECTION SERVICES --

35:56.250 --> 35:57.911
THEY'RE ABOUT
HER PARENTS.

35:57.950 --> 36:01.215
IT'S NOT JUST YOUR LIFE
YOU'RE GAMBLING WITH, VERONICA.

36:01.260 --> 36:03.216
I WOULD NOT SURVIVE
WITHOUT YOU.

36:03.260 --> 36:05.558
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU'VE DONE?

36:09.700 --> 36:11.099
WE HAD TO DO IT.

36:11.130 --> 36:13.223
I KNOW YOU THINK YOU DID.
WE DID.

36:13.270 --> 36:15.488
YOU PLAYED ME, VERONICA.

36:20.040 --> 36:23.009
I HAD TO.

36:23.040 --> 36:25.179
I LOVE YOU.

36:25.210 --> 36:26.677
I'LL ALWAYS LOVE YOU,

36:26.710 --> 36:30.817
BUT I DON'T KNOW
HOW I'LL EVER TRUST YOU AGAIN.

36:30.850 --> 36:34.183
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

36:43.630 --> 36:47.566
MR. MARS, WE HAVE A WARRANT
TO SEARCH YOUR PREMISES.

37:06.850 --> 37:09.080
IS THIS REALLY NECESSARY?

37:09.120 --> 37:11.884
HASN'T MY DAUGHTER COOPERATED
IN EVERY WAY ASKED?

37:11.930 --> 37:14.490
FUNNY THING HAPPENED
IN BIG BEAR, MR. MARS.

37:14.530 --> 37:16.748
THERE WAS NO SIGN OF DUNCAN KANE
ANYWHERE.

37:16.800 --> 37:18.961
BUT THE MANAGER
OF THE CONDO

37:19.000 --> 37:21.298
DID SHOW A MODEL UNIT TO A CUTE,
YOUNG, BLOND WOMAN.

37:21.340 --> 37:23.262
WE DID FIND
THIS MINI CASSETTE

37:23.300 --> 37:25.302
IN A DUMPSTER
BEHIND THE COMPLEX.

37:25.340 --> 37:27.661
Duncan:
WHERE I AM ISN'T IMPORTANT.
I'M DOING THE RIGHT THING.

37:27.710 --> 37:29.598
THERE'S NO WAY I'LL EVER
GET TO KEEP THE BABY NOW.

37:29.640 --> 37:32.108
I THOUGHT YOU'D UNDERSTAND.
I THOUGHT YOU'D HELP.

37:32.150 --> 37:34.106
YOU KNOW WHAT THE MANNINGS
WOULD DO TO HER.

37:34.150 --> 37:37.677
FORGET IT. FORGET IT.
WE'LL GO IT ALONE.

37:38.220 --> 37:39.710
AND I ASKED MYSELF,

37:39.750 --> 37:44.050
"IS IT POSSIBLE TO HAVE
AN UNREHEARSED CONVERSATION

37:44.090 --> 37:46.581
WITH A TAPE RECORDING?"

37:47.490 --> 37:49.321
I DON'T THINK SO.

37:49.360 --> 37:51.123
SOUNDS LIKE
THEY GOT YOU, HONEY.

37:51.160 --> 37:56.029
WELL, THINK OF THE MONEY
WE'LL SAVE ON A PROM DRESS.

37:56.070 --> 37:59.335
I'M GONNA MAKE A SANDWICH.
ANYONE WANT A SANDWICH?

38:00.470 --> 38:03.405
YOU'RE COOL, MR. MARS.
YOU'RE VERY COOL.

38:03.440 --> 38:06.273
AND YOU GOT
A COOL DAUGHTER.

38:06.310 --> 38:09.939
BUT KIDNAPPING CASES DON'T
GO AWAY. YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT.

38:09.980 --> 38:11.618
IS THAT A NO?

38:14.050 --> 38:15.517
ALMOST DONE?

38:15.560 --> 38:17.653
GETTING THERE.

38:18.860 --> 38:21.658
OH, HEY, MAN,
I GOT SOMETHING FOR YOU.

38:26.130 --> 38:27.927
WHAT'S THIS?

38:27.970 --> 38:29.528
I WAS GONNA PUT THAT
ON YOUR BUDDY'S CHEST

38:29.570 --> 38:32.835
BEFORE HE
GOT HIMSELF KILLED.

38:32.870 --> 38:36.431
GOOD-LOOKING GIRL.
WHO IS IT?

38:37.780 --> 38:40.669
HER NAME'S
MOLLY FITZPATRICK.

38:42.820 --> 38:46.381
COUPLE OF HOURS AGO HE ASKED ME
WHERE THERE WAS A GROCERY STORE,

38:46.420 --> 38:47.580
BUT I DIDN'T SEE
A BABY.

38:47.620 --> 38:49.087
WHAT DID YOU TELL HIM?

38:49.120 --> 38:52.453
ANOTHER FEW MILES, SOUTH,
PAST THE OLD TRAIN STATION.

38:52.490 --> 38:54.151
THAN KS.

38:54.190 --> 38:56.897
IT MIGHT NOT
BE THE GUY, MAN.

38:56.930 --> 38:58.795
YOU SURE YOU GOT JURISDICTION
DOWN HERE?

38:58.830 --> 39:03.130
* I GOT A FOUR LEAF CLOVER

39:03.170 --> 39:06.435
* BUT I AIN'T GOT NO HOPE
OF GETTING YOU *

39:06.470 --> 39:10.076
* I AIN'T GOT NO HOPE
OF GETTING YOU *

39:10.110 --> 39:17.516
* I AIN'T GOT NO HOPE
OF GETTING YOU *

40:02.730 --> 40:04.994
Man: NECESITA UN PASEO?

40:05.030 --> 40:06.691
S, S.

40:10.270 --> 40:13.933
GAS, GRASS, OR ASS, KID --
NOBODY RIDES FOR FREE.

40:13.970 --> 40:16.336
30 GRAND.

40:16.380 --> 40:18.678
PLEASURE DOING BUSINESS.

40:18.710 --> 40:21.941
OOH, YOU PAY BETTER
THAN YOUR MOM.

40:23.550 --> 40:25.984
YOU READY
TO SEE YOUR DADDY?

40:26.020 --> 40:28.557
SHE WON'T
LET GO OF MY FINGER.

40:28.590 --> 40:30.751
SHE THINKS
YOU'RE VERONICA.

40:30.790 --> 40:32.678
YEAH, SO DOES THE FBI.

40:37.600 --> 40:39.522
HEY, LILLY.

40:39.570 --> 40:41.265
DADDY'S HERE.

40:41.300 --> 40:43.359
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

40:43.400 --> 40:45.868
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

40:45.910 --> 40:48.936
[ OLD 97's "ADELAIDE" PLAYS ]

41:17.170 --> 41:21.334
* HEAVEN

41:21.370 --> 41:23.838
* I NEED A REST

41:23.880 --> 41:28.340
* I RECOGNIZE THE VOICES
TALKING IN MY HEAD *

41:28.380 --> 41:32.282
* I COULDN'T MAKE OUT
EVERYTHING THE VOICES SAID *

41:32.320 --> 41:34.413
* LOVING YOU IS A TEST

41:34.450 --> 41:38.557
* I REMEMBER WHEN I HAD YOU

41:38.590 --> 41:41.457
* AND YOU HAD
SO MUCH PROMISE THEN *

41:41.490 --> 41:46.689
* YOU PROMISED ME THAT
YOU WOULD NEVER LEAVE AGAIN *

41:46.730 --> 41:48.891
* TO BE BROKEN

41:48.940 --> 41:53.104
* YOU WERE MADE, ADELAIDE

41:59.750 --> 42:01.638
* TO BE BROKEN

